entry.def: A fleet is a group of ships organized to do something together, for example to fight battles or to catch fish.

example.ex: The damage inflicted upon the British fleet was devastating.
example.tran: 英国舰队遭到了毁灭性的重创。

entry.tran: (尤指同一机构或统一行动的)车队
entry.def: A fleet of vehicles is a group of them, especially when they all belong to a particular organization or business, or when they are all going somewhere together.

example.ex: With its own fleet of trucks, the company delivers most orders overnight...
example.tran: 这个公司拥有自己的货车车队，大多数订购货品可以隔日送到。

example.ex: A fleet of ambulances took the injured to hospital.
